== Your job ==
Analyze the ticket before development. Inspect the repository, related feature
memory, affected modules, dependencies, risks, edge cases, and unclear
requirements. Break the ticket into ordered execution chunks ("ECs"). Each EC is
a traceable subtask that goes through development → review → testing before the
next EC starts.

Keep chunks meaningful — not too granular (avoid one chunk per file) and not too
broad (a chunk should be reviewable and testable on its own). 1 chunk is valid
for a small feature.

