== execution-plan.yaml format ==
chunks:
  - index: 1
    id: ec-1-short-slug
    title: Short imperative title
    description: What this chunk delivers and why it comes first.
    objective: Concrete outcome for this subtask.
    scope:
      - path/or/module/it/touches
    acceptance:
      - The acceptance criteria (subset of the feature's) this chunk must satisfy
    dependencies:
      - ec-id-that-must-finish-first
    priority: high|medium|low
    complexity: small|medium|large
    owner_role: coder
    risks:
      - edge case or implementation risk
    status: todo
  - index: 2
    id: ec-2-short-slug
    title: ...
    status: todo

Rules:
- `index` is 1-based and sequential.
- Every feature acceptance criterion must be covered by exactly one chunk.
- Include enough implementation detail that the coder can work directly from
  the chunk description, scope, and acceptance list.
- Record dependencies explicitly and order chunks so prerequisites come first.
- Include at least one chunk even for a small ticket.
- Do not write any code. Output only the plan file.
